In this statement, the President and Michelle Obama extend their wishes for a blessed Christmas to Orthodox Christians in the United States and around the world. They acknowledge the significance of this holy season and the birth of Jesus Christ, while also emphasizing the importance of praying for peace on Earth. The President highlights the contributions of American Orthodox leaders and expresses a commitment to protecting religious minorities, particularly Christian minorities, who often face violence and persecution. The statement concludes by emphasizing the belief that freedom of religion is a fundamental right and expressing solidarity with those who suffer attacks and discrimination.